						               													<description>Horizon 1 is a solitaire science fiction settlement-building game of strategy, resource management, and above all, growth and survival.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game is an entry in the 2021 Solitaire Print and Play Contest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Overview:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Priority 1: Establish and develop the Horizon 1 settlement on planet Cerberus.&amp;#10;Priority 2: Maximise settlement population.&amp;#10;Priority 3: Extract as many minerals as possible from the planet crust.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your settlers make planetfall on Cerberus, 2.6 light years from Earth. As the Governor of the Horizon 1 settlement, your task is to ensure their safety, to build facilities in which they can live and work and, most importantly, to research and understand this strange new world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turn structure:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played over a series of game turns. Each game turn consists of a number of phases, performed in the order below.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Resource collection phase. Collect food and ore resources.&amp;#10;     Research phase. Check if scientific breakthroughs occur, and (optionally) change research focus or projects.&amp;#10;     Movement phase. Move units, explore terrain, prospect, and move aliens.&amp;#10;     Building phase (optional). Use Engineer (ENGINR) units to build / demolish modules.&amp;#10;     Combat phase. Any aliens present engage colonial militia in combat.&amp;#10;     Event phase. Draw and resolve an event card, and flip the Day / Night counter.&amp;#10;     Status check phase. Update position of status counters on the status board. Do an approval check.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends immediately when any of the following conditions occur:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Life support module is destroyed.&amp;#10;     Settler rebellion occurs.&amp;#10;     There are no cards remaining in the draw pile of event cards.&amp;#10;     Settlement population (POP) reaches zero.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the game ends, your Victory Points (VPs) total = population + ore mined. Some event and technology cards also provide VPs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
